Meet was set for Togo on March 7Event postponed owing to Covid-19 dampens athletes’ spirits in Embu Team Kenya officials have moved to restore athletes’ morale at St Mark’s Kigari Teachers Training College in Embu, where they are camping, following the postponement of the sixth Africa Cross Country Championship that had been scheduled to be held in Lome, Togo on March 7. 

Head coach Francis Kamau and team manager Kithinji Maragara spent several hours talking to the athletes who were demoralised after the event was put off because of Covid-19 health risks. 



